	(text "POWER  --  2S LiPo -> AP63203 3V3 (2A) + TPS54302 6V motor rail (3A); SW5=logic, SW6=motors"
		(at 10 190 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "34035172-3121-4bc0-a1e7-74df3a69e4e1")
	)
	(text "+3V3 is the regulated logic rail: ESP32-S3, mux, IMU, encoder VCC, PT pull-ups,\nindicator drivers and IR LED current. VM_6V feeds ONLY the TB6612 VM pins."
		(at 200 100 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.2 2.2)))
		(uuid "0be62eeb-e60e-4ef2-b814-fc269dfb2fad")
	)
	(text "VBAT_SENSE = pack (0-8.4V) x 39/139 <= 2.36V on ADC1 IO7 (direct).\nVBUS_SENSE = 5V x 15/25 <= 3.15V on IO9. PACK-LEVEL monitoring only\n(per-cell/balance removed). Firmware cutoff: 6.6V pack floor (3.3V/cell avg);\nthe 6V motor rail stays in regulation across the 6.6-8.4V window."
		(at 20 20 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.2 2.2)))
		(uuid "e956414a-65bb-445e-af8a-1afc5a5dbc05")
	)
	(text "MOTOR DRIVER (TB6612FNG, SMD)  --  2x N20-with-encoder motors"
		(at 10 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "14478d58-f775-4dca-92be-3935077b6eed")
	)
	(text "Bare TB6612FNG (U2, SSOP-24) in IN/IN PWM mode: PWMA/PWMB tied 3V3, AIN/BIN = LEDC\n(IN1=PWM,IN2=0 fwd-coast; IN1=PWM,IN2=1 rev-brake). VM = regulated 6.0V rail (TPS54302,\n3A limit) gated by SW6; STBY pulled high (R55) -- motor kill = SW6 + IN pins' internal\npull-downs. Decoupling: C30 220uF/16V alu + C11 10uF/25V + C12 100nF on VM, C14 on VCC."
		(at 10 258 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "1928c80f-92f1-4e9d-9d1d-adf710d17cca")
	)
	(text "10k pull-ups on all 4 encoder lines -- defensive: N20-encoder wire-color-to-\nfunction mapping is unverified for the exact unit ordered (see PROJECT_NOTES.md),\nand encoder output stage (open-drain vs push-pull) isn't confirmed either. A pull-up\nis required if open-drain and harmless if push-pull.\nRev 7.2: J5/J6 are JST ZH B6B-ZR in the ROBU CABLE order (M1,VCC,C1,C2,GND,M2) --\nthe motor's factory plug goes straight in, zero soldering. METER-VERIFY pins 2/5\n(VCC/GND) against the actual cable before first plug-in; swap crimps 2/5 if reversed."
		(at 10 400 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "98aa77bf-8735-475a-9463-c7b186e4170d")
	)
	(text "CONTROLLER  --  ESP32-S3-WROOM-1 (dual-core 240MHz, FreeRTOS, WiFi): control + telemetry"
		(at 300 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "730a5c27-7f08-4f89-8829-09c88bad972c")
	)
	(text "ESP32-S3-WROOM-1 on FreeRTOS: 6 wall sensors DIRECT on ADC1 IO1-IO6 (a fired pair is\nsampled in parallel), line array via U4 (IO7 + IO11-13), battery IO8, TB6612 on\nIO9/10/38/45, buzzer IO46 (straps 45/46 = idle-low outputs ONLY -- never add pull-ups),\nencoders IO43/44/47/48 (PCNT hardware quadrature via GPIO matrix), JTAG on the real\nJTAG quad IO39-42 -> J8 (ESP-Prog). Buttons: SW1=IO0 (start/BOOT), SW3=IO35, SW4=IO36\n(internal pull-ups). USB-C (rear) on the native USB pads = flash + console; UART0\npins repurposed as encoder inputs. Every analog net sits on ADC1 (IO1-IO8)."
		(at 300 368 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "9ca861e8-bcd9-4d05-9be4-35639683a6aa")
	)
	(text "USER INTERFACE  --  3 buttons"
		(at 600 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "837fcc28-7b8d-4197-a2d5-8cb02ad8fe9e")
	)
	(text "Buttons are lettered on the silkscreen: A=SW1, B=SW3, C=SW4, RST=SW2.\nSW1/A = USER_BTN on IO0: start-run button AND the BOOT strap (hold A, tap RST\n-> ROM download mode). External 10k pull-up R10 keeps the strap solid.\nSW3/SW4 = USER_BTN2/3 on IO35/IO36 (menu/select UX): active-low, firmware enables the\ninternal pull-ups -- no external resistors. NOTE: on octal-PSRAM (-R8) modules IO35/36\ndo not exist; buttons 2/3 are the sacrificial feature (control is unaffected).\nSW2 (reset) lives in the controller section on ESP_EN."
		(at 600 260 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "bb2964d1-a43d-4fe1-bbe0-a7e0f0073372")
	)
	(text "IMU  --  BNO055 9-axis on I2C (IO18=SDA, IO21=SCL, IO37=INT), addr 0x28; internal osc"
		(at 600 420 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "b8361982-6d91-4989-954a-ba81d9a96b18")
	)
	(text "BNO055 mid-line placement (user requirement): geometric center of rotation sensing.\nMag data is calibration-grade only on a motor robot (1A at 5mm ~ Earth field); the\nyaw-rate loop uses the gyro. Fusion runs on-chip (100Hz NDOF) or raw gyro at 523Hz."
		(at 600 560 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "782fb421-afeb-401c-acdf-f9cd470288d8")
	)
	(text "IR SENSOR ARRAY  --  6 wall sensors (direct ADC; line array + mux U4 removed)"
		(at 10 420 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "1daafd09-a74e-41e1-a8b1-f6de16b73e34")
	)
	(text "ONE HEF4067 (line array only -- user decision 2026-07-15: wall sensors are read\ndirectly on ESP32 ADC1 pins). Each sensor: phototransistor (collector -> 47k pull-up\nto +3V3 AND to its readout node; emitter -> GND) + IR LED (anode -> current-limit\nresistor -> +3V3; cathode -> its GROUP's low-side switch). Emitters are GANGED:\nfront pair / diagonal pair / side pair / all-8 line bank, each on one BSS138 driven\nby its own GPIO (IO15/16/17/14). Firing a wall pair and sampling BOTH its ADC pins\nin the same pulse halves scan time vs the old serial mux walk; read bright, read\nambient (group off), subtract. Current-limit: wall 33R (~50mA pulsed) / line 120R\n(~15mA, latch-capable for line-follow + indicators). UKMARS-practice grouping keeps\nmutually-staring sensors on different groups."
		(at 150 460 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "614389c8-a163-49ee-9fa1-cd0aaa64870d")
	)
	(text "WALL-SENSOR INDICATORS  --  6 top-side LEDs, LED ON = wall seen (PMOS, inverted node)"
		(at 10 760 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "44ec0e53-8ce2-4218-a7fc-c9b717209b81")
	)
	(text "STATUS / POWER / RGB LEDs"
		(at 600 600 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "2fa607cf-5ba0-4c10-985d-2da7fc4e16b8")
	)
